       <div class="solutions__entry">
        <div class="solutions__content">
         <h1 style="color: #333f48; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; text-align: center;">
          EAB in Action
         </h1>
         <h2 style="color: #333f48; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-bottom: 0px; text-align: center;">
          Making education smarter isn't just our job. It's our passion. Keep reading to see how we put best practices to work.
         </h2>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- content block item -->
       <div class="solutions__entry">
        <div class="solutions__logo" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_1_dvLogo">
         <a href="/technology/academic-performance-solutions/resources/infographics/bottlenecks" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_1_lnkImg">
          <img alt="" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_1_img" src="/-/media/EAB/Technology/Academic-Performance-Solutions/Infographics/Bottleneck/36174-APS-IG-213px.jpg"/>
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="solutions__content">
         <h3 style="color: #333f48; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-left: 60px;">
          Infographic of the Week
         </h3>
         <p style="color: #666666; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-left: 60px;">
          If student persistence and success are on your mind, so should any barrier that may get in a student’s way. Course bottlenecks slow students’ time to degree and cause them to incur additional costs. Learn about the different types of bottlenecks—and how you can alleviate them to help more students graduate on time.
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- content block item -->
       <div class="solutions__entry">
        <div class="solutions__logo" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_2_dvLogo">
         <a href="/research-and-insights/advancement-forum/studies/2017/donor-investor-imperative" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_2_lnkImg">
          <img alt="" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_2_img" src="/-/media/EAB/ucla-logotype-main-11-600x286.jpg"/>
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="solutions__content">
         <h3 style="padding-left: 60px">
          Best Practice of the Week
         </h3>
         <p style="padding-left: 60px">
          Donors who visit college giving pages often struggle to find the causes that matter to them most. The university buries specific gift designations in long drop-down menus that few donors take the trouble to navigate. Consequently, donors fail to see something they feel passionate about supporting and leave without making a gift. Instead, UCLA's new giving website organizes funds into 14 causes and mirrors the functionality of a crowdfunding site.
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <!-- content block item -->
       <div class="solutions__entry">
        <div class="solutions__logo" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_3_dvLogo">
         <a href="https://www.chronicle.com/article/What-Can-the-CEO-of-a/242161" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_3_lnkImg">
          <img alt="" id="main_1_hpmainpublic_3_contentblockitems_3_img" src="/-/media/EAB/Homepage/big logo.png"/>
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="solutions__content">
         <h3 style="color: #333f48; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-left: 60px;">
          EAB in the News
         </h3>
         <p style="color: #666666; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; padding-left: 60px;">
          "What Can the CEO of a $1.6-Billion Enrollment-Services Giant Tell Us About the Student Life Cycle?" Hear from EAB's CEO David Felsenthal in this profile originally featured in the Chronicle of Higher Education.
         </p>
        </div>
